fields.intro: Introductory text for the training page goes here. It could be about two to three sentences, but this example will just be two.
fields.description:
Investigative reporting is not a very popular practice for many journalists in Nigeria but it holds the key to correcting some of the wrongs in the society, opening long-held secrets, ensuring wrongdoers get due punishment for their actions while celebrating good conduct of people, innovations by organisations and sterling accomplishments in the face of challenges.

This course will explore issues, ethics and challenges of investigative reporting by analysing and discussing outstanding and controversial examples of this genre of journalism while participants work on real-world investigative project ideas.

It will stimulate participants to identify, develop and follow through investigative story ideas, research and interviewing techniques as well as personal safety while in the trenches.
fields.audience: Editors, reporters, civil society activists, journalism teachers, etc.
